TITLE: U. of Michigan agrees to settle students' sex-abuse lawsuit
SUMMARY: The University of Michigan has reached an agreement to settle a lawsuit brought by students who sought to force changes in how the school protects the campus from sexual misconduct

TITLE: NATO extends Stoltenberg term for a year due to Russia's war
SUMMARY: NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg will remain in his role for an extra year to help steer the 30-nation military organization through the security crisis sparked by Russia’s war on Ukraine

TITLE: 18-year-old dies after shooting at party venue in Dallas
SUMMARY: Officials say an 18-year-old man who was one of 10 people shot outside of a party venue in Dallas has died

TITLE: Russia-Ukraine live updates: 6,000 Mariupol residents allegedly now in Russian camps
SUMMARY: Live updates on the Russia-Ukraine crisis.

TITLE: US says it will accept up to 100,000 Ukrainian refugees
SUMMARY: Administration officials did not specify a timeline for accepting these refugees.

TITLE: WATCH:  Entangled humpback whale cleared of marine debris off Maui
SUMMARY: A female humpback whale traveling with a male and a calf has been rescued after it was found entangled in a line with a large bundle of marine debris attached.

TITLE: WATCH:  Basketball rescue during March Madness
SUMMARY: After players and the referee at a March Madness game failed to retrieve a basketball wedged behind a backboard, two cheerleaders stepped in to help and the crowd went wild.

TITLE: Americans applying for jobless aid is lowest since 1969
SUMMARY: Unemployment benefit applications last week fell to its lowest in 52 years

TITLE: NATO: 7,000 to 15,000 Russian troops dead in Ukraine
SUMMARY: NATO is estimating that 7,000 to 15,000 Russian soldiers have been killed.

TITLE: North Korea fires suspected long-range missile toward sea
SUMMARY: North Korea has fired possibly its biggest intercontinental ballistic missile toward the sea, raising the ante in a pressure campaign aimed at forcing the US and other rivals to accept it as a nuclear power and remove crippling sanctions

TITLE: Police: 7 children hospitalized after given sleeping pills
SUMMARY: A house full of unsupervised children in Virginia were given sleeping pills by another child, causing them to be hospitalized Wednesday evening, police said

TITLE: Boy, 13, pleads no contest to shooting at deputies
SUMMARY: A 13-year-old Florida boy who broke out of a children's home with a teenage girl and fired on deputies during a shootout last year has pleaded no contest to attempted murder

TITLE: 4 dead, 1 injured, after apparent fall from Swiss building
SUMMARY: Swiss police say three adults and a child have died and a teenager was seriously injured in a fall from a seven-story residential building in the lakeside town of Montreux

TITLE: Arrest made in mass shooting at car show that killed 1, injured 26
SUMMARY: Brandon Deandra Knight was arrested after being released from the hospital Wednesday morning and charged with battery and aggravated assault.

TITLE: Cop accused of kneeling on girl resigns from school, citing 'strain' on family
SUMMARY: An off-duty police officer in Kenosha resigned from his role in the school district amid an investigation into the tactics he used to restrain a 12 year-old girl.

TITLE: Family of man killed by sheriff's deputy say he was in mental health crisis
SUMMARY: The family of Irvin Moorer Charley, who was killed by sheriff's deputies in South Carolina, say he was having a mental health crisis.

TITLE: LIVE:  ABC News Live
SUMMARY: 24/7 coverage of breaking news and live events

SUMMARY: A funnel cloud was spotted in Chalmette, Louisiana, amid reports of damaging tornadoes in the New Orleans area.

TITLE: WATCH:  Tornado hits New Orleans
SUMMARY: A suspected EF-3 twister hit St. Bernard's Parish in New Orleans.

TITLE: WATCH:  Couple survives tornado by hiding in their bathroom
SUMMARY: A couple described their experience surviving a tornado that destroyed their Texas home.

SUMMARY: A family on a fishing trip got a fishy fright when a great white shark leaped out of the water behind their boat.

SUMMARY: People ran to safety inside a store as a storm tore through a parking lot in Round Rock, Texas, amid tornado warnings across the state.

SUMMARY: Strong winds lifted a bounce house off the ground in Hickory, North Carolina, narrowly missing a child. No injuries were reported.
